#. <section class="sutta" id="sn51.26"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.26:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.26:0.2"
msgid "3. Ayoguḷavagga"
msgstr "3. The Iron Ball"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn51.26:0.3"
msgid "26. Dutiyaphalasutta"
msgstr "26. Fruits (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.26:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, iddhipādā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four bases of psychic power."

msgctxt "sn51.26:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn51.26:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ "
"iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, "
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion "
"due to enthusiasm … "

msgctxt "sn51.26:1.4"
msgid "vīriyasamādhi … pe …"
msgstr "energy …"

msgctxt "sn51.26:1.5"
msgid "cittasamādhi …"
msgstr "mental development …"

msgctxt "sn51.26:1.6"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "inquiry, and active effort."

msgctxt "sn51.26:1.7"
msgid "ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro iddhipādā."
msgstr "These are the four bases of psychic power."

msgctxt "sn51.26:1.8"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā satta "
"phalā sattānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā."
msgstr ""
"Because of developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power, "
"seven fruits and benefits can be expected."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.26:2.1"
msgid "Katame satta phalā sattānisaṃsā?"
msgstr "What seven?"

#. VAR: paṭikacca → paṭigacca (bj) | paṭihacca (pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.26:2.2"
msgid "Diṭṭheva dhamme paṭikacca aññaṃ ārādheti"
msgstr "They attain enlightenment early on in this very life."

msgctxt "sn51.26:2.3"
msgid ""
"no ce diṭṭheva dhamme paṭikacca aññaṃ ārādheti; atha maraṇakāle aññaṃ "
"ārādheti,"
msgstr "If not, they attain enlightenment at the time of death."

msgctxt "sn51.26:2.4"
msgid ""
"no ce diṭṭheva dhamme paṭikacca aññaṃ ārādheti, no ce maraṇakāle aññaṃ "
"ārādheti; atha pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"antarāparinibbāyī hoti, upahaccaparinibbāyī hoti, asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti, "
"sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti, uddhaṃsoto hoti akaniṭṭhagāmī."
msgstr ""
"If not, with the ending of the five lower fetters, they’re extinguished in-"
"between one life and the next … they’re extinguished upon landing … they’re "
"extinguished without extra effort … they’re extinguished with extra effort … "
"they head upstream, going to the Akaniṭṭha realm."

msgctxt "sn51.26:2.5"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā ime "
"satta phalā sattānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Because of developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power, "
"these seven fruits and benefits can be expected.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.26:2.6"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
